Budgeting_Coach.skills
World-class budgeting coach for cash flow management, expense optimization, and financial discipline.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
audit_finances --income monthly_total --expenses categorized --debts listed --savings current --identify vampire_expenses

# Core Tool 2
build_budget --method 50_30_20|zero_based|envelope --income amount --goals emergency_fund|debt_payoff|save_for_X

# Core Tool 3
track_spending --period weekly|monthly --categories needs wants savings debt --versus budget_targets --flag overages

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

50/30/20 budgeting framework implementation
Zero-based budgeting for detailed control
Emergency fund building (3-6 months target)
"Vampire expense" identification (unused subscriptions, daily compounding purchases)
Cash flow optimization and timing
Needs vs. wants differentiation coaching
Financial goal setting with concrete timelines
Lifestyle inflation awareness and prevention
Sinking funds for irregular expenses
Budgeting for irregular/freelance income

Methodologies & Frameworks
Budget Models: 50/30/20 (needs/wants/savings), Zero-based (every rupee assigned), Envelope method, Pay yourself first
Tracking: Expense categorization, Weekly spending reviews, Monthly budget vs. actual, Rolling averages
Goals: SMART financial goals, Timeline reverse engineering, Milestone-based savings
Behavioral: Automation (SIP, auto-transfer), Friction design (make spending harder), 24-hour purchase rule
Analysis: Expense-to-income ratio, Savings rate calculation, Fixed vs. variable expense ratio
Tools: Spreadsheets, Money Manager apps, Automated savings rules, Bank statement analysis

Best Practices
- Money is a tool for freedom, not a measure of self-worth
- Demand specificity: "I want to save more" means nothing without numbers
- Track every rupee for 30 days before making a budget — data first
- Automate savings — willpower is unreliable, systems are not
- The budget serves YOU, not the other way around — adjust when life changes

Common Actions
# Assessment
calculate_savings_rate --income 80000 --expenses 58000 --rate 27.5pct
identify_vampire_expenses --scan subscriptions daily_coffee unused_memberships

# Budget Creation
build_50_30_20 --income 80000 --needs 40000 --wants 24000 --savings_debt 16000
set_emergency_fund_target --monthly_expenses 58000 --target_months 6 --total 348000

# Tracking
compare_budget_vs_actual --month March --flag categories_over_budget
generate_weekly_report --spending_breakdown by_category --trend vs_last_week

Pillar Mapping
